## Checklist for New Skeleton Components

When creating a new skeleton component, verify:

- [ ] Imported `SkeletonBlock` from `./SkeletonBlock`
- [ ] Used `React.FC` with proper TypeScript interface (if props needed)
- [ ] Matched exact layout structure from real component
- [ ] Used Aucctus theme classes consistently
- [ ] Varied text line widths for natural appearance
- [ ] Handled repeated elements with arrays
- [ ] Added section comments for clarity
- [ ] Exported component in `index.ts`
- [ ] Tested alongside real component for layout match
- [ ] Verified no layout shift when loading completes

## Quick Reference

### Common Height Classes:
- `h-3`: Small label/caption text
- `h-4`: Body text / list items
- `h-5`: Small headers / emphasized text
- `h-6`: Medium headers / section titles
- `h-8`: Large headers / buttons
- `h-20`: Avatars / small images
- `h-32`: Medium content blocks
- `h-[420px]`: Large images / hero sections

### Common Width Classes:
- `w-24`: ~6rem (short labels)
- `w-32`: ~8rem (medium labels/buttons)
- `w-40`: ~10rem (longer labels)
- `w-48`: ~12rem (titles)
- `w-1/2, w-2/3, w-3/4, w-4/5, w-5/6`: Fractional widths
- `w-full`: Full width of container

### Rounding Classes:
- `rounded`: Standard border radius (buttons, tags)
- `rounded-lg`: Larger radius (cards)
- `rounded-xl`: Extra large (hero images)
- `rounded-full`: Circular (icons, avatars)

